---
// ScenariosSection.astro
---

<section class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 py-24 sm:py-32" id="scenarios">
  <div class="text-center mb-16 reveal">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-accent/10 border border-accent/15 text-accent text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">
      Why it matters
    </div>
    <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(28px,3.5vw,44px)] font-bold tracking-[-0.03em] mb-4">
      Real-life bottlenecks
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-secondary text-[15px] sm:text-base">
      Critical issues that traditional Wi-Fi signal bars can't reveal.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-4">
    
    <!-- Scenario 1 -->
    <div class="bg-bg-elevated border border-white/5 rounded-3xl p-6 sm:p-7 flex gap-5 reveal transition-all duration-300 hover:border-white/10 hover:bg-[#0c0c11] shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(0,0,0,0.15)] group">
      <div class="w-1 rounded-full shrink-0 bg-accent/70 group-hover:scale-y-105 transition-transform duration-300"></div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h3 class="text-[16px] font-bold mb-1.5 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
          Your upload is stuck at 
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-accent bg-accent-dim border border-accent/15 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-md font-semibold">0 KB/s</code>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Dropbox isn't syncing, iCloud backups have paused, or your corporate VPN is choking. The menu bar signal says full. Traffy reveals the zero throughput instantly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scenario 2 -->
    <div class="bg-bg-elevated border border-white/5 rounded-3xl p-6 sm:p-7 flex gap-5 reveal reveal-delay-1 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-white/10 hover:bg-[#0c0c11] shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(0,0,0,0.15)] group">
      <div class="w-1 rounded-full shrink-0 bg-accent/70 group-hover:scale-y-105 transition-transform duration-300"></div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h3 class="text-[16px] font-bold mb-1.5 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
          Your Zoom call freezes mid-meeting
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The router is close, signal is 100%. But your upload bandwidth just tanked to
          <code class="font-mono text-[13px] text-accent bg-accent-dim border border-accent/15 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-md font-semibold">0.2 Mbps</code>.
          Now you know exactly why your audio is stuttering.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scenario 3 -->
    <div class="bg-bg-elevated border border-white/5 rounded-3xl p-6 sm:p-7 flex gap-5 reveal reveal-delay-2 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-white/10 hover:bg-[#0c0c11] shadow-[0_4px_20px_rgba(0,0,0,0.15)] group">
      <div class="w-1 rounded-full shrink-0 bg-accent/70 group-hover:scale-y-105 transition-transform duration-300"></div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h3 class="text-[16px] font-bold mb-1.5 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
          Video streaming buffer drops to zero
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Your movie freezes on the screen. Traffy lets you monitor download rates in real-time, helping you instantly isolate whether it is a local device crash or network-side provider lag.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
